	<h1>Presentation</h1>
	<p class="tagline">Chart scaling and screenshot tools for documentation and review.</p>

	<h2 id="chart-scaling">Chart Scaling</h2>
	<p><strong>Keep your chart readable at any zoom level.</strong></p>
	<p>Smart Auto-Scroll detects when you scroll back through history and disables autoscroll automatically. Scroll back to the present and it re-enables. No more fighting the chart to review past price action.</p>
	<p>Fixed Scale locks your current zoom level using CHART_SCALEFIX. The chart won't rescale when new bars form or price moves - useful when you need consistent visual proportions across screenshots.</p>
	<p>Head and Tail Margins add asymmetric padding based on where price sits in the visible range. Default is 20% on each side, preventing price from hugging the edges. When price is near the top, more margin appears above; near the bottom, more below.</p>
	<p>ATR Range uses the Daily ATR as a minimum range floor. This prevents over-zooming on quiet periods where the visible high-low range is tiny. The chart always shows at least the D1 ATR worth of price range, keeping context visible.</p>
	<p>ATR Period is configurable from 1 to 100 bars, defaulting to 14. The adaptive scaling algorithm takes the maximum of visible high-low range and D1 ATR, then adds margins.</p>

	<h2 id="screenshots">Screenshots</h2>
	<p><strong>Capture your analysis for review or sharing.</strong></p>
	<p>The Screenshot button captures the current chart view exactly as displayed. The Panorama button captures an extended width - configurable from 2x to 6x your normal view - for documenting longer price sequences.</p>
	<p>The Split button converts panorama images to printable pages using ImageMagick. Wide screenshots become a series of standard-sized pages suitable for printing or PDF assembly.</p>
	<p>All screenshots save to MQL5/Files/ with timestamps. The default directory is PrismChart/Screenshots, configurable via MT5 input parameter.</p>
	<p>The presentation dialog automatically hides before capture, so your screenshots show clean charts without UI overlay.</p>
</DocsLayout>
